1
00:00:41,792 --> 00:00:45,963
MY ROYAL NEMESIS

2
00:00:51,760 --> 00:00:53,971
<i>The caller you are trying</i>
<i>to reach is unavailable.</i>

3
00:00:54,054 --> 00:00:56,181
<i>You will be transferred to voicemail</i>

4
00:00:56,265 --> 00:00:58,016
<i>after the beep.</i>

5
00:00:59,643 --> 00:01:01,144
Shin Seo-ri, I was wrong.

6
00:01:01,228 --> 00:01:03,397
It's all my fault.
Just pick up your phone.

7
00:01:04,898 --> 00:01:07,234
I'll wait here until you come home.

8
00:01:12,781 --> 00:01:16,410
JANGSUGOL PORK BACKBONE STEW

9
00:01:17,911 --> 00:01:19,079
- Shin Seo-ri.
- Step back.

10
00:01:19,162 --> 00:01:20,539
- Step back.
- Get out of my way.

11
00:01:20,622 --> 00:01:22,207
Let me through! I'm her guardian.

12
00:01:22,291 --> 00:01:23,667
Let go!

13
00:01:23,750 --> 00:01:24,835
Shin Seo-ri.

14
00:01:24,918 --> 00:01:26,628
Shin Seo-ri, wake up.

15
00:01:26,712 --> 00:01:28,046
Wake up, Shin Seo-ri!

16
00:01:30,173 --> 00:01:31,758
EMERGENCY MEDICAL CENTER

17
00:01:38,348 --> 00:01:40,267
- Please clear the way.
- Make way.

18
00:01:40,350 --> 00:01:42,102
- Please step back.
- Coming through!

19
00:01:42,185 --> 00:01:43,395
Coming through!

20
00:01:43,478 --> 00:01:45,272
CURRENT TIME 19:27
SURGICAL TIME, ANESTHESIA TIME

21
00:02:16,428 --> 00:02:17,971
Your Highness.

22
00:02:21,767 --> 00:02:24,728
Your Highness, are you awake?

23
00:02:24,811 --> 00:02:27,439
- Hurry. Go fetch the physician!
- Yes, ma'am!

24
00:02:30,984 --> 00:02:32,402
<i>Your Highness?</i>

25
00:02:32,486 --> 00:02:34,696
Your Highness, are you awake?

26
00:02:35,530 --> 00:02:36,615
<i>Where am I…</i>

27
00:02:36,698 --> 00:02:38,867
Do you recognize me?

28
00:02:43,622 --> 00:02:47,167
EPISODE 11
WHAT LIES ON THE HIDDEN PATH

29
00:02:51,797 --> 00:02:53,423
<i>What are you doing here…</i>

30
00:02:57,636 --> 00:02:58,720
What is wrong with her?

31
00:02:58,804 --> 00:03:01,098
Why can she not move
when she is clearly awake?

32
00:03:01,181 --> 00:03:03,975
Her blood flow and vital energy
have yet to be restored.

33
00:03:04,059 --> 00:03:06,937
Still, she has escaped the deathly trance.
Let us wait and see.

34
00:03:07,020 --> 00:03:07,938
<i>Deathly trance?</i>

35
00:03:08,021 --> 00:03:10,857
With breath restored,
once blood flow and vital energy return,

36
00:03:10,941 --> 00:03:12,067
she should be able to move.

37
00:03:12,150 --> 00:03:14,403
So are we to just wait indefinitely?

38
00:03:14,486 --> 00:03:16,863
It is truly a miracle
she has made it this far.

39
00:03:16,947 --> 00:03:19,282
Even if she was shielded
with the herbal antidote,

40
00:03:19,366 --> 00:03:21,243
- her organs were damaged by the poison…
<i>- Poison?</i>

41
00:03:21,326 --> 00:03:24,538
- …and have not fully healed.
<i>- Have I truly returned?</i>

42
00:03:24,621 --> 00:03:25,914
<i>But what is wrong with my body…</i>

43
00:03:25,997 --> 00:03:28,125
She is stable for now.

44
00:03:28,208 --> 00:03:31,211
I shall prepare the remainder
of the <i>Chuhontang</i> and calamus extract.

45
00:03:31,294 --> 00:03:33,171
All right. Make haste.

46
00:03:48,270 --> 00:03:50,731
<i>Hey. Stop.</i>

47
00:03:51,314 --> 00:03:52,607
<i>Can you not hear my voice?</i>

48
00:03:52,691 --> 00:03:53,900
<i>Hey!</i>

49
00:03:57,696 --> 00:03:58,989
<i>Am I</i>

50
00:03:59,072 --> 00:04:00,782
<i>trapped</i>

51
00:04:00,866 --> 00:04:02,284
<i>in this body?</i>

52
00:04:09,416 --> 00:04:11,585
A small bleed has caused
some swelling in the brain.

53
00:04:11,668 --> 00:04:14,880
Fortunately, medication was enough.
No surgery was needed.

54
00:04:14,963 --> 00:04:16,840
No serious external injuries
aside from bruising.

55
00:04:16,923 --> 00:04:18,133
So her life isn't in danger?

56
00:04:18,216 --> 00:04:20,552
That's right. As long as there are
no complications,

57
00:04:20,635 --> 00:04:22,888
she should regain consciousness
in a few days.

58
00:04:24,181 --> 00:04:26,558
The problem is Chairman Cha.

59
00:04:27,642 --> 00:04:28,518
Tell me.

60
00:04:28,602 --> 00:04:30,270
The surgery was successful,

61
00:04:30,353 --> 00:04:33,565
but we must monitor him
until his breathing stabilizes.

62
00:04:36,902 --> 00:04:39,613
<i>This afternoon, Chail Group's</i>
<i>Chairman Cha Dal-su</i>

63
00:04:39,696 --> 00:04:41,740
<i>was critically injured</i>
<i>in a drunk driving accident</i>

64
00:04:41,823 --> 00:04:42,949
<i>involving a truck.</i>

65
00:04:43,033 --> 00:04:44,075
- My goodness.
<i>- The driver…</i>

66
00:04:44,159 --> 00:04:46,495
<i>had a blood alcohol level of 0.12%</i>

67
00:04:46,578 --> 00:04:48,872
<i>and was found to be heavily intoxicated.</i>

68
00:04:49,748 --> 00:04:51,917
- Father.
- Father.

69
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:54,085
What an absolute nightmare this is.

70
00:04:54,169 --> 00:04:56,129
Father. Our poor father.

71
00:04:57,255 --> 00:04:59,674
Se-gye, I heard you went straight
to the accident scene.

72
00:04:59,758 --> 00:05:01,092
How did you know to go there?

73
00:05:01,176 --> 00:05:02,761
- What do you mean?
- Well, think about it.

74
00:05:02,844 --> 00:05:05,222
The accident is strange,
as is how quickly you showed up.

75
00:05:05,305 --> 00:05:06,598
What are you trying to say?

76
00:05:06,681 --> 00:05:08,767
Stop it.

77
00:05:08,850 --> 00:05:10,602
Is this really the time for that?

78
00:05:10,685 --> 00:05:11,728
I'm just merely raising

79
00:05:11,812 --> 00:05:13,980
a reasonable suspicion.

80
00:05:14,064 --> 00:05:15,565
I mean, the logic just isn't there.

81
00:05:15,649 --> 00:05:18,360
A car crashing into a restaurant
in broad daylight

82
00:05:18,443 --> 00:05:21,446
isn't exactly something
you can easily wrap your head around.

83
00:05:27,702 --> 00:05:29,246
Is Grandfather okay?

84
00:05:29,329 --> 00:05:30,831
He just came out of surgery.

85
00:05:30,914 --> 00:05:33,792
The doctor said it went well,
so we must be patient.

86
00:05:36,127 --> 00:05:38,672
Se-gye, you don't look well at all.

87
00:05:38,755 --> 00:05:40,924
Do you want to step outside
for some fresh air?

88
00:05:41,007 --> 00:05:41,925
I'm fine.

89
00:05:45,136 --> 00:05:46,721
GRANDMOTHER OK-SUN

90
00:05:50,767 --> 00:05:52,602
<i>Sorry to bother you.</i>

91
00:05:52,686 --> 00:05:55,480
<i>But I just can't seem to reach Seo-ri.</i>

92
00:05:55,564 --> 00:05:57,148
Is everything okay in Seoul?

93
00:06:00,694 --> 00:06:01,820
Yes.

94
00:06:02,696 --> 00:06:04,281
Everything is fine.

95
00:06:04,364 --> 00:06:05,323
<i>Don't worry.</i>

96
00:06:05,407 --> 00:06:08,201
<i>I'll take care of your restaurant too.</i>

97
00:06:08,285 --> 00:06:10,537
So please don't worry about a thing.

98
00:06:10,620 --> 00:06:12,455
My goodness.

99
00:06:12,956 --> 00:06:16,084
Hearing you say that
is nice and reassuring,

100
00:06:16,167 --> 00:06:17,460
but please don't overdo it.

101
00:06:17,544 --> 00:06:20,589
<i>It'd be nice if things went</i>
<i>the way you planned,</i>

102
00:06:20,672 --> 00:06:23,758
but nothing comes easy in life.

103
00:06:25,552 --> 00:06:26,887
I'm plenty grateful as it is.

104
00:06:27,846 --> 00:06:29,806
<i>Thanks to you, I can finally relax.</i>

105
00:06:29,890 --> 00:06:32,183
<i>I've always had this knot in my chest</i>

106
00:06:32,267 --> 00:06:34,144
because I was worried
she'd wither away alone.

107
00:06:34,227 --> 00:06:36,396
Now I can finally breathe easy.

108
00:06:37,397 --> 00:06:40,567
<i>My Seo-ri takes after me.</i>
<i>She can be a bit feisty.</i>

109
00:06:40,650 --> 00:06:43,528
<i>She just runs her mouth</i>
<i>without thinking sometimes.</i>

110
00:06:43,612 --> 00:06:45,947
Even so, just say that it's lovely.

111
00:06:46,031 --> 00:06:48,909
When someone close to you
keeps calling you lovely,

112
00:06:48,992 --> 00:06:51,786
<i>you really do become lovely.</i>
<i>It's human nature.</i>

113
00:06:54,331 --> 00:06:55,206
All right.

114
00:06:57,667 --> 00:06:58,627
I will.

115
00:06:59,794 --> 00:07:01,463
I promise I will.

116
00:07:10,805 --> 00:07:11,973
<i>Do not follow me.</i>

117
00:07:12,057 --> 00:07:14,225
<i>- I cannot stand the sight of you.</i>
- As if.

118
00:07:15,352 --> 00:07:17,729
Your grandmother was right.

119
00:07:17,812 --> 00:07:19,981
You're feisty and difficult.

120
00:07:20,065 --> 00:07:22,651
You throw hurtful words around
without thinking.

121
00:07:23,276 --> 00:07:24,569
But what can I do?

122
00:07:25,362 --> 00:07:27,572
Even if you can't stand me,
we have no other choice.

123
00:07:27,656 --> 00:07:29,741
No matter how much you push me away,

124
00:07:29,824 --> 00:07:31,868
I'm going to stick right by your side.

125
00:07:50,845 --> 00:07:52,263
When I was a kid,

126
00:07:52,889 --> 00:07:54,641
I used to love the days

127
00:07:54,724 --> 00:07:57,352
I would hold my mom's hand
to go to your house.

128
00:07:57,435 --> 00:07:59,646
There was so much delicious food.

129
00:08:00,271 --> 00:08:01,439
The house was huge.

130
00:08:01,523 --> 00:08:05,151
I even thought it would be nice
if Mom and I lived there with you.

131
00:08:08,071 --> 00:08:10,240
Since you were alone anyway.

132
00:08:10,782 --> 00:08:13,910
I wished you were my father.

133
00:08:22,877 --> 00:08:24,337
When I gave you the transplant,

134
00:08:24,421 --> 00:08:27,424
I'd be lying if I said
I didn't have any ulterior motive.

135
00:08:28,508 --> 00:08:32,053
But it made me feel
like we became connected somehow.

136
00:08:32,137 --> 00:08:33,555
You and me.

137
00:08:33,638 --> 00:08:35,390
Even though I meant nothing to you.

138
00:08:38,143 --> 00:08:40,562
<i>So what's your point?</i>

139
00:08:40,645 --> 00:08:42,063
Did you really come here

140
00:08:42,147 --> 00:08:44,816
thinking <i>that</i> gave you
leverage over Se-gye?

141
00:08:44,899 --> 00:08:46,067
Some trifling brat?

142
00:08:46,151 --> 00:08:47,027
Because I know

143
00:08:47,110 --> 00:08:49,946
Jin-u still breaks your heart,
after all this time.

144
00:08:50,030 --> 00:08:52,198
I couldn't let Se-gye betray you as well.

145
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:55,744
I shot myself in the foot.

146
00:08:55,827 --> 00:08:57,871
You had such wicked eyes, even as a boy.

147
00:08:57,954 --> 00:09:00,081
I knew this day would come.

148
00:09:00,915 --> 00:09:03,001
I couldn't refuse Hye-suk's request,

149
00:09:03,084 --> 00:09:05,336
and now I'm paying for it dearly.

150
00:09:08,214 --> 00:09:10,675
Why do you think
I've kept you by my side

151
00:09:10,759 --> 00:09:12,302
for all these years?

152
00:09:13,011 --> 00:09:15,013
You're nothing but a debt to me.

153
00:09:15,096 --> 00:09:19,225
A debt my only sister left behind
with our blood ties as collateral.

154
00:09:19,309 --> 00:09:20,268
And you dare

155
00:09:20,351 --> 00:09:22,645
disgrace my grandson?

156
00:09:23,354 --> 00:09:25,065
A lowly bastard like you!

157
00:09:26,941 --> 00:09:30,236
If I'm the debt you owe my mother,

158
00:09:31,112 --> 00:09:32,697
then that debt…

159
00:09:35,575 --> 00:09:37,827
You can start paying me back now.

160
00:09:38,453 --> 00:09:42,165
Be sure to include the interest
for my loyalty over the last 20 years.

161
00:09:50,173 --> 00:09:53,384
If you do, I'm willing
to show you some leniency,

162
00:09:54,219 --> 00:09:55,720
Uncle.

163
00:10:17,075 --> 00:10:17,951
RESEARCHER

164
00:10:20,870 --> 00:10:22,247
WHISTLEBLOWER CONFESSION:
BIOJEI…

165
00:10:23,581 --> 00:10:26,417
- Their image is completely ruined.
- Who would buy it now?

166
00:10:32,841 --> 00:10:33,925
<i>Sir.</i>

167
00:10:34,008 --> 00:10:34,884
The news…

168
00:10:34,968 --> 00:10:36,219
The news?

169
00:10:40,348 --> 00:10:42,892
<i>Chail Group, a cornerstone</i>
<i>of Korea's corporate world,</i>

170
00:10:42,976 --> 00:10:45,103
<i>is facing a seismic shift</i>
<i>in its succession.</i>

171
00:10:45,186 --> 00:10:47,021
<i>A chain of setbacks has been hitting</i>

172
00:10:47,105 --> 00:10:49,983
<i>this top-ten conglomerate</i>
<i>in rapid succession,</i>

173
00:10:50,066 --> 00:10:52,068
<i>putting its future in jeopardy.</i>

174
00:10:52,152 --> 00:10:53,695
<i>Cha Se-gye of the Cha Family</i>

175
00:10:53,778 --> 00:10:56,489
<i>is under fire, and a major earnings miss</i>

176
00:10:56,573 --> 00:10:59,075
<i>has only fueled the controversy.</i>

177
00:10:59,159 --> 00:11:03,705
<i>The backlash is mounting</i>
<i>after carcinogenic substances</i>

178
00:11:03,788 --> 00:11:07,041
<i>were discovered in Dynaestie,</i>
<i>a new line from Cha's cosmetics startup,</i>

179
00:11:07,125 --> 00:11:09,169
<i>- Biojei.</i>
- The rest to the CEO's office!

180
00:11:09,252 --> 00:11:12,672
<i>Biojei was quick to dismiss</i>
<i>the claims as baseless,</i>

181
00:11:12,755 --> 00:11:15,091
<i>but whistleblower reports</i>
<i>of harmful substances</i>

182
00:11:15,175 --> 00:11:17,385
<i>in an upcoming product</i>
<i>have been pouring in.</i>

183
00:11:17,468 --> 00:11:21,055
<i>An online boycott of the brand</i>
<i>has spread like wildfire.</i>

184
00:11:21,764 --> 00:11:24,601
<i>A past power-abuse scandal resurfacing</i>
<i>amid everything else</i>

185
00:11:24,684 --> 00:11:26,060
<i>has sent their stock into freefall.</i>

186
00:11:26,144 --> 00:11:27,645
<i>In the fallout, Kaiserman Capital,</i>

187
00:11:27,729 --> 00:11:29,689
<i>Dynaestie's largest known investor,</i>

188
00:11:29,772 --> 00:11:31,733
<i>exercised its conversion rights</i>

189
00:11:31,816 --> 00:11:34,444
<i>to take the top shareholder</i>
<i>position at Biojei,</i>

190
00:11:34,527 --> 00:11:37,363
<i>positioning itself as a white knight.</i>

191
00:11:37,447 --> 00:11:39,657
<i>With Kaiserman</i>
<i>now participating in management,</i>

192
00:11:39,741 --> 00:11:43,328
<i>the business world is watching</i>
<i>to see if Biojei can bounce back.</i>

193
00:11:43,411 --> 00:11:45,371
<i>Meanwhile,</i>
<i>Chail Group Chairman Cha Dal-su</i>

194
00:11:45,455 --> 00:11:48,416
<i>has fallen into a coma</i>
<i>following a sudden accident.</i>

195
00:11:48,499 --> 00:11:50,627
<i>Management convened</i>
<i>an emergency shareholders' meeting</i>

196
00:11:50,710 --> 00:11:52,545
<i>in a bid to shore up</i>
<i>the falling stock price.</i>

197
00:11:52,629 --> 00:11:55,215
<i>At the meeting, Choi Mun-do,</i>
<i>Chairman Cha Dal-su's nephew</i>

198
00:11:55,298 --> 00:11:58,051
<i>and current president of Chail E&C,</i>

199
00:11:58,134 --> 00:12:00,720
<i>was approved to take over</i>
<i>leadership of the group,</i>

200
00:12:00,803 --> 00:12:03,806
<i>with 69.3% in favor and 30.7% against.</i>

201
00:12:03,890 --> 00:12:06,100
<i>As Chail Group bypasses</i>
<i>third-generation succession</i>

202
00:12:06,184 --> 00:12:07,769
<i>in favor of a collateral line,</i>

203
00:12:07,852 --> 00:12:10,230
<i>industry watchers are closely following</i>
<i>whether this marks</i>

204
00:12:10,313 --> 00:12:12,232
<i>a new precedent</i>
<i>for chaebol succession in Korea.</i>

205
00:12:12,315 --> 00:12:14,234
Then what happens to the owner's family?

206
00:12:14,317 --> 00:12:15,735
The daughters are figureheads,

207
00:12:15,818 --> 00:12:17,737
and the one grandson
got cut off at the knees.

208
00:12:17,820 --> 00:12:18,988
It's a lost cause.

209
00:12:19,072 --> 00:12:21,366
This is why you must align yourself
with the right people.

210
00:12:21,449 --> 00:12:22,825
Don't you think?

211
00:12:30,500 --> 00:12:32,669
This will be your desk.

212
00:12:32,752 --> 00:12:35,755
There's no handover,
so you can just start working right away.

213
00:12:35,838 --> 00:12:37,131
Yes, sir.

214
00:12:37,757 --> 00:12:39,968
Shouldn't you be packing up?

215
00:12:40,051 --> 00:12:41,344
Right.

216
00:12:43,763 --> 00:12:47,267
So you're telling me this was
all Choi Mun-do's master plan?

217
00:12:47,350 --> 00:12:49,727
Kaiserman Capital was the Trojan Horse.

218
00:12:49,811 --> 00:12:51,562
Director Jang was a spy.

219
00:12:51,646 --> 00:12:54,065
You know, I always got
a weird vibe from him.

220
00:12:54,607 --> 00:12:57,819
I thought you said he was a rare grown-up
among all the clueless Gen Zers.

221
00:12:57,902 --> 00:12:59,279
That was…

222
00:13:00,071 --> 00:13:03,116
To be fair, he is on the older side
for a cosmetics startup.

223
00:13:03,199 --> 00:13:04,325
Exactly,

224
00:13:04,409 --> 00:13:06,744
the boomer held it in well.

225
00:13:06,828 --> 00:13:08,162
A founding figure of Chail Group,

226
00:13:08,246 --> 00:13:10,915
but he was used and discarded
by Chairman Cha.

227
00:13:10,999 --> 00:13:13,918
He must have grabbed
President Choi Mun-do as a lifeline.

228
00:13:14,585 --> 00:13:16,421
It's fine. Just be patient.

229
00:13:16,504 --> 00:13:18,589
It never ends well for people
who act like Lü Bu.

230
00:13:18,673 --> 00:13:19,757
Just wait and see.

231
00:13:19,841 --> 00:13:21,092
If Director Jang is Lü Bu,

232
00:13:21,175 --> 00:13:23,303
what does that make President Choi Mun-do?

233
00:13:24,345 --> 00:13:25,638
Dong Zhuo?

234
00:13:26,681 --> 00:13:27,640
Isn't it obvious?

235
00:13:27,724 --> 00:13:29,517
He's Cao Cao.

236
00:13:29,600 --> 00:13:31,978
<i>A ruthless poker face.</i>

237
00:13:32,061 --> 00:13:34,814
Seo-jun, how is it being in Korea?

238
00:13:34,897 --> 00:13:36,065
Are you happy?

239
00:13:36,149 --> 00:13:37,317
Yes, I am.

240
00:13:38,484 --> 00:13:41,029
It would've been even better

241
00:13:41,112 --> 00:13:43,197
if my nanny could've come.

242
00:13:44,157 --> 00:13:45,116
She said

243
00:13:45,199 --> 00:13:47,327
she couldn't come
because she has her family over there.

244
00:13:47,410 --> 00:13:49,203
She wanted me to tell you
that she's sorry.

245
00:13:49,287 --> 00:13:51,497
If that's why, it's fine.

246
00:13:51,581 --> 00:13:53,207
Because I have a dad now too.

247
00:14:04,093 --> 00:14:06,387
Hey, what did the assistant director say?

248
00:14:06,471 --> 00:14:08,639
He said the shooting schedule
can't be adjusted, right?

249
00:14:08,723 --> 00:14:11,476
I asked him, but he was merciless.

250
00:14:11,559 --> 00:14:12,435
He said he can't upend

251
00:14:12,518 --> 00:14:14,354
the cast's schedule
over one supporting actor.

252
00:14:14,437 --> 00:14:17,315
It seems like there's even a chance
they might drop her.

253
00:14:20,735 --> 00:14:23,112
Gosh. Ji-hyo.

254
00:14:23,738 --> 00:14:26,824
Your shoot ended at dawn yesterday.
You should've just rested.

255
00:14:26,908 --> 00:14:29,744
She's an actor in the same agency
and the same drama.

256
00:14:29,827 --> 00:14:31,079
Imagine if I didn't come.

257
00:14:31,162 --> 00:14:33,915
They'll say I'm rotten to the core,
call me a complete diva,

258
00:14:33,998 --> 00:14:35,333
and drag me through the mud.

259
00:14:35,416 --> 00:14:37,877
Well, you're right about that.

260
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:40,046
But since Seo-ri

261
00:14:40,129 --> 00:14:41,881
is unconscious right now,

262
00:14:41,964 --> 00:14:44,217
leaving this will be more than enough.

263
00:14:45,968 --> 00:14:48,346
She's unconscious?

264
00:15:03,194 --> 00:15:06,572
She looks fine on the outside,
so why is she still unconscious?

265
00:15:06,656 --> 00:15:08,032
I'm not sure.

266
00:15:08,116 --> 00:15:10,785
The doctor said she wasn't badly hurt,

267
00:15:11,285 --> 00:15:12,662
so I'm not really sure.

268
00:15:14,872 --> 00:15:17,250
Then she'll definitely miss
the shoot in two days.

269
00:15:17,333 --> 00:15:18,751
Fair grounds for firing.

270
00:15:18,835 --> 00:15:19,919
The whole cast and crew

271
00:15:20,002 --> 00:15:22,296
shouldn't have to take
a hit over one supporting actor.

272
00:15:22,380 --> 00:15:23,256
That's just too much.

273
00:15:23,339 --> 00:15:24,549
Even so,

274
00:15:24,632 --> 00:15:27,593
that's not something you say
to a colleague in the hospital.

275
00:15:29,637 --> 00:15:30,888
Mr. Baek Gwang-nam.

276
00:15:30,972 --> 00:15:32,265
You really sounded

277
00:15:32,348 --> 00:15:34,225
like her real manager just now.

278
00:15:35,685 --> 00:15:37,019
Sorry.

279
00:15:39,605 --> 00:15:41,065
Want to know something?

280
00:15:41,774 --> 00:15:43,985
Chances are, nobody's searched
Shin Seo-ri's name

281
00:15:44,068 --> 00:15:45,194
more than I have.

282
00:15:45,278 --> 00:15:46,362
I really hated

283
00:15:46,446 --> 00:15:48,114
Shin Seo-ri when we were child actors.

284
00:15:49,115 --> 00:15:49,991
<i>You can have this.</i>

285
00:15:50,074 --> 00:15:51,200
I have a lot left.

286
00:15:54,704 --> 00:15:56,664
Shin Seo-ri, quit showing off.

287
00:15:59,417 --> 00:16:01,794
I didn't care about anything else.
I just wanted to beat her.

288
00:16:01,878 --> 00:16:03,754
I thought if I just beat her, I'd be set.

289
00:16:03,838 --> 00:16:06,549
I've probably watched <i>Sonagi</i>
more than anyone.

290
00:16:06,632 --> 00:16:09,051
I turned it on as soon as
I woke up in the morning.

291
00:16:09,135 --> 00:16:10,386
But one day,

292
00:16:11,262 --> 00:16:13,764
she got into some sort of accident.

293
00:16:13,848 --> 00:16:15,892
She took about six months off

294
00:16:15,975 --> 00:16:18,102
and came back
a completely different person.

295
00:16:18,186 --> 00:16:21,022
She wasn't the Shin Seo-ri I knew.

296
00:16:21,105 --> 00:16:23,774
The girl who used to shine
in front of the camera.

297
00:16:29,489 --> 00:16:31,866
Do you know how dumbfounded I was then?

298
00:16:31,949 --> 00:16:34,202
My goal suddenly disappeared.

299
00:16:36,037 --> 00:16:39,207
Since then, I've had this weird anxiety
that just won't go away.

300
00:16:40,333 --> 00:16:43,503
But why are you telling me this?

301
00:16:46,797 --> 00:16:48,257
Just because.

302
00:16:50,510 --> 00:16:52,887
Maybe because you're her manager?

303
00:16:52,970 --> 00:16:55,556
Isn't that why you just took her side?

304
00:16:59,268 --> 00:17:01,354
Don't worry about the shooting schedule.

305
00:17:01,437 --> 00:17:02,939
I'll take care of it.

306
00:17:03,022 --> 00:17:04,440
What? How exactly?

307
00:17:04,524 --> 00:17:05,900
Well…

308
00:17:05,983 --> 00:17:08,110
I'll just tell them I have
a European photoshoot.

309
00:17:08,194 --> 00:17:11,113
If the lead says postpone,
what choice do they have?

310
00:17:11,197 --> 00:17:12,573
I'm off.

311
00:17:13,324 --> 00:17:14,283
Right.

312
00:17:18,955 --> 00:17:20,873
- Hold this for a second.
- Sure.

313
00:17:21,582 --> 00:17:22,833
Wait, what are you doing…

314
00:17:25,503 --> 00:17:27,838
<i>Get well soon, my friend.</i>

315
00:17:29,924 --> 00:17:31,092
Wow.

316
00:17:31,175 --> 00:17:33,636
Also, keep what I just told you
a secret from Shin Seo-ri.

317
00:17:33,719 --> 00:17:35,972
I'll sue you if you tell her.
You can bet on it.

318
00:17:42,853 --> 00:17:43,854
I'm off.

319
00:17:48,025 --> 00:17:51,445
Wow, how can she just switch
between hot and cold like that?

320
00:18:05,918 --> 00:18:08,212
<i>This place is undoubtedly Joseon.</i>

321
00:18:08,296 --> 00:18:10,047
<i>Then what was that place?</i>

322
00:18:10,131 --> 00:18:13,467
<i>Was all of that truly just a dream?</i>

323
00:18:13,551 --> 00:18:15,261
<i>How could it all…</i>

324
00:18:16,637 --> 00:18:18,681
<i>have just been a dream?</i>

325
00:18:19,599 --> 00:18:21,976
Seo-ri. Wake up, Seo-ri.

326
00:18:25,021 --> 00:18:26,397
<i>Who was that?</i>

327
00:18:26,480 --> 00:18:28,482
<i>Someone definitely called my name.</i>

328
00:18:49,086 --> 00:18:50,838
Did you know?

329
00:18:50,921 --> 00:18:53,341
Even after Your Highness left,

330
00:18:53,424 --> 00:18:55,801
the red comet burns on.
Day and night, unwavering.

331
00:18:55,885 --> 00:18:58,137
Quite farcical, really.
They called it an ill-omened star

332
00:18:58,220 --> 00:19:00,973
threatening the Crown
and sentencing you to drink poison for it.

333
00:19:01,057 --> 00:19:02,308
<i>An ill-omened star?</i>

334
00:19:02,391 --> 00:19:04,810
However, that star started

335
00:19:04,894 --> 00:19:07,563
moving last night.

336
00:19:09,440 --> 00:19:11,609
Ever since Your Highness returned.

337
00:19:11,692 --> 00:19:14,403
<i>"Returned"? What do you know?</i>

338
00:19:14,487 --> 00:19:17,865
Life and death are intertwined
like the warp and weft.

339
00:19:17,948 --> 00:19:21,702
Therefore, Your Highness
can live even if you die.

340
00:19:21,786 --> 00:19:23,204
Whether it is here…

341
00:19:25,498 --> 00:19:27,041
or there.

342
00:19:34,090 --> 00:19:36,217
<i>What? What are you doing?</i>

343
00:19:49,480 --> 00:19:51,649
There is not much time left.

344
00:19:52,775 --> 00:19:55,653
When the red comet finds its place again,
and your vital energy returns,

345
00:19:55,736 --> 00:19:58,197
it will guide Your Highness's soul.

346
00:20:00,282 --> 00:20:01,909
Back to your body here.

347
00:20:02,451 --> 00:20:04,745
<i>"Guide it"? What does that mean?</i>

348
00:20:06,247 --> 00:20:08,165
So you must sever them.

349
00:20:11,460 --> 00:20:13,462
Both the bad ties and the good.

350
00:20:14,630 --> 00:20:16,632
Every last knotted thread of old.

351
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:19,093
<i>No.</i>

352
00:20:19,635 --> 00:20:21,262
<i>What I want is…</i>

353
00:20:24,724 --> 00:20:27,727
When the red comet finds its place again,
and your vital energy returns,

354
00:20:27,810 --> 00:20:29,729
it will guide Your Highness's--

355
00:20:30,980 --> 00:20:32,022
What the…

356
00:20:32,565 --> 00:20:33,941
What was that?

357
00:20:35,735 --> 00:20:37,653
Jeez. My goodness.

358
00:20:37,737 --> 00:20:39,238
What just came and went?

359
00:20:40,322 --> 00:20:41,615
No. Absolutely not.

360
00:20:41,699 --> 00:20:43,117
Hold on.

361
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:46,078
Begone, evil spirit.
Away with you, evil spirit.

362
00:20:49,331 --> 00:20:53,043
Yes, the resort will proceed
without a hitch.

363
00:20:53,711 --> 00:20:55,713
We'll announce
the construction schedule

364
00:20:55,796 --> 00:20:57,840
at the upcoming
50th anniversary celebration.

365
00:20:58,716 --> 00:21:00,134
Of course.

366
00:21:00,760 --> 00:21:02,803
I must do what I can
to help the mayor out.

367
00:21:02,887 --> 00:21:04,680
Yes, I'll be in touch.

368
00:21:13,606 --> 00:21:16,025
Send a car to Mayor Jang.

369
00:21:16,734 --> 00:21:17,651
Yes, sir.

370
00:21:17,735 --> 00:21:19,487
But you have a guest.

371
00:21:32,708 --> 00:21:35,377
It's been a while, President Choi.

372
00:21:36,253 --> 00:21:38,672
Or should I call you Chairman Choi now?

373
00:21:38,756 --> 00:21:40,591
What brings you here, Ms. Mo?

374
00:21:40,674 --> 00:21:42,968
There's something we need to discuss.

375
00:21:45,304 --> 00:21:47,598
How would you like
to work together with me?

376
00:21:48,265 --> 00:21:51,060
The Biojei shares under Kaiserman.

377
00:21:51,143 --> 00:21:53,062
Let Mochang buy them out.

378
00:21:55,940 --> 00:21:57,316
- The shares?
- Yes.

379
00:21:57,399 --> 00:22:01,403
I'll guarantee a substantial premium.
120% of the current market value.

380
00:22:01,487 --> 00:22:04,240
Naturally, the partnership we formed
around Songjin Resort

381
00:22:04,323 --> 00:22:07,535
will also be maintained going forward.

382
00:22:07,618 --> 00:22:11,497
And if you partner
with Mochang's resort chain,

383
00:22:11,580 --> 00:22:15,042
I can guarantee the fastest expansion
into the Southeast Asian market.

384
00:22:15,709 --> 00:22:16,961
But I have a condition.

385
00:22:18,337 --> 00:22:19,296
A condition?

386
00:22:19,380 --> 00:22:22,174
I'd like Mochang to take
full charge of the TF team

387
00:22:22,258 --> 00:22:24,218
overseeing all Songjin Resort operations.

388
00:22:33,269 --> 00:22:35,521
<i>Filming postponed due</i>
<i>to an actor's external commitments.</i>

389
00:22:35,604 --> 00:22:38,315
<i>Just like that,</i>
<i>she pulled off what I couldn't.</i>

390
00:22:38,399 --> 00:22:40,568
Maybe because you're her manager?

391
00:22:40,651 --> 00:22:42,987
Isn't that why you just took her side?

392
00:22:44,363 --> 00:22:45,614
Manager, my foot.

393
00:22:46,490 --> 00:22:48,534
Look at the mess I'm in because of you.

394
00:22:48,617 --> 00:22:51,036
I never wanted to be a manager.

395
00:22:52,037 --> 00:22:55,541
Damn it. I was really going to quit
after this month.

396
00:22:59,670 --> 00:23:01,547
Just look at this. See?

397
00:23:01,630 --> 00:23:03,090
How can I quit if you…

398
00:23:09,972 --> 00:23:12,558
Hey, are you awake?

399
00:23:13,142 --> 00:23:14,768
Are you okay?

400
00:23:16,645 --> 00:23:19,106
I was so worried
because you weren't waking up.

401
00:23:20,774 --> 00:23:21,942
You…

402
00:23:22,026 --> 00:23:23,110
What? What was that?

403
00:23:24,153 --> 00:23:25,237
Down…

404
00:23:25,321 --> 00:23:26,864
You must be exhausted.

405
00:23:27,656 --> 00:23:30,284
I'm here. Just take your time.

406
00:23:30,367 --> 00:23:32,328
Pipe down.

407
00:23:37,958 --> 00:23:40,127
SEOBU POLICE STATION

408
00:23:40,210 --> 00:23:43,297
<i>These documents show</i>
<i>that carcinogenic substances were detected</i>

409
00:23:43,380 --> 00:23:45,799
in a cosmetic product your company
had scheduled for release.

410
00:23:45,883 --> 00:23:49,053
Directives to secretly swap ingredients
for cheap carcinogenic materials

411
00:23:49,136 --> 00:23:50,930
were also found.

412
00:23:52,139 --> 00:23:56,101
These were submitted by a whistleblower,
along with a declaration of conscience.

413
00:24:00,898 --> 00:24:02,858
Can you actually tell the difference

414
00:24:02,942 --> 00:24:05,986
between a real whistleblower
and a troll from <i>this,</i> Inspector?

415
00:24:06,070 --> 00:24:07,988
You'd pin a hit-and-run on someone

416
00:24:08,072 --> 00:24:09,949
even if their car was stolen
and used for it.

417
00:24:10,032 --> 00:24:10,991
Are you saying

418
00:24:11,075 --> 00:24:13,577
that there's a spy inside your company?

419
00:24:13,661 --> 00:24:14,620
Is that it?

420
00:24:14,703 --> 00:24:18,415
Then I can summon and investigate
your close associates one by one?

421
00:24:18,499 --> 00:24:20,250
It's definitely not anyone in my office.

422
00:24:20,334 --> 00:24:23,253
Just leave them out of your summons,
inquiries, or whatever else.

423
00:24:23,337 --> 00:24:24,296
Are you sure?

424
00:24:24,380 --> 00:24:26,799
You said it yourself.
Planting something like this is nothing

425
00:24:26,882 --> 00:24:27,841
for an insider.

426
00:24:29,635 --> 00:24:31,845
People sell their conscience
for chump change nowadays.

427
00:24:31,929 --> 00:24:33,430
This is nothing.

428
00:24:35,724 --> 00:24:36,892
Exactly.

429
00:24:36,976 --> 00:24:40,187
I'm saying nobody would risk
their life for some chump change.

430
00:24:40,270 --> 00:24:41,230
Why?

431
00:24:44,483 --> 00:24:45,985
Because if you cross me like that,

432
00:24:46,068 --> 00:24:49,613
I'll make sure your family can't find work
or even plant a foot in this country

433
00:24:49,697 --> 00:24:51,740
for three generations.

434
00:25:04,044 --> 00:25:05,546
<i>Where are you?</i>

435
00:25:06,714 --> 00:25:08,590
<i>I woke up,</i>
<i>and you were nowhere to be found.</i>

436
00:25:08,674 --> 00:25:10,634
You should be right by my side.

437
00:25:11,176 --> 00:25:12,511
<i>Where did you gallivant off to?</i>

438
00:25:12,594 --> 00:25:13,846
Shin Seo-ri.

439
00:25:14,680 --> 00:25:15,889
Just be patient.

440
00:25:15,973 --> 00:25:17,224
I'm on my way.

441
00:25:17,307 --> 00:25:20,102
We're in the middle of an investigation.
Where do you think you're going?

442
00:25:20,185 --> 00:25:21,061
Inspector,

443
00:25:21,145 --> 00:25:23,230
I need to leave immediately.

444
00:25:23,939 --> 00:25:25,774
Let's call it a day for now.

445
00:25:25,858 --> 00:25:27,568
And let me offer you a deal.

446
00:25:48,797 --> 00:25:49,840
Damn it.

447
00:26:08,150 --> 00:26:09,026
Cha Se-gye.

448
00:26:12,196 --> 00:26:14,823
You are drenched in sweat.
Where have you been?

449
00:26:14,907 --> 00:26:15,949
You…

450
00:26:19,828 --> 00:26:21,663
Why are you sitting up? You're a patient.

451
00:26:21,747 --> 00:26:23,582
Lie down. What did the doctor say?

452
00:26:23,665 --> 00:26:24,750
I am perfectly fine.

453
00:26:24,833 --> 00:26:27,711
Then why didn't you wake up
for over a week?

454
00:26:27,795 --> 00:26:31,006
Were you trying to make me
have an aneurysm? Damn it.

455
00:26:34,843 --> 00:26:36,261
Just stay there.

456
00:26:36,345 --> 00:26:38,639
I'll go get the doctor,
so get a full checkup--

457
00:26:38,722 --> 00:26:40,307
Can you not just stay?

458
00:26:42,017 --> 00:26:43,977
Stay by my side.

459
00:26:48,023 --> 00:26:49,775
If you were so worried,

460
00:26:49,858 --> 00:26:52,069
you should have stayed right by my side.

461
00:26:52,152 --> 00:26:53,529
And not go gallivanting--

462
00:26:53,612 --> 00:26:55,072
No, I…

463
00:26:59,201 --> 00:27:00,744
Hold on. This is unfair.

464
00:27:01,537 --> 00:27:03,831
I was right by your side the whole time.

465
00:27:03,914 --> 00:27:06,834
I stepped out for just a second,
and you wake up then.

466
00:27:10,546 --> 00:27:12,005
Then hurry up.

467
00:27:29,898 --> 00:27:31,316
It finally feels real.

468
00:27:32,943 --> 00:27:34,903
I was afraid this was a dream too.

469
00:27:36,405 --> 00:27:37,823
I was so worried.

470
00:27:40,075 --> 00:27:42,744
That dream was so long,
and it felt so real.

471
00:27:44,413 --> 00:27:46,039
But you were not there.

472
00:27:47,207 --> 00:27:48,667
And I could not wake up.

473
00:27:50,085 --> 00:27:53,005
I wondered what I would do
if I were trapped there forever.

474
00:27:54,673 --> 00:27:56,800
I was terrified.

475
00:28:02,973 --> 00:28:04,308
Are you an idiot?

476
00:28:05,100 --> 00:28:06,185
That's not scary at all.

477
00:28:39,843 --> 00:28:42,387
Unbelievable. Choi Mun-do…

478
00:28:43,013 --> 00:28:44,890
Turns out he's one nasty piece of work.

479
00:28:44,973 --> 00:28:48,977
When did he win over the board
to railroad this through?

480
00:28:49,061 --> 00:28:52,981
I told you ages ago that he always had
a weird look in his eyes.

481
00:28:53,065 --> 00:28:54,816
Don't go stirring things up.

482
00:28:55,442 --> 00:28:59,112
We can't trust anyone right now,
not the police or the prosecutors.

483
00:28:59,196 --> 00:29:00,280
And you?

484
00:29:00,364 --> 00:29:01,990
Can I trust you?

485
00:29:02,074 --> 00:29:05,118
Are you suspecting me right now?
In the middle of all this?

486
00:29:05,869 --> 00:29:07,996
I don't have a single stake
in this with that kid.

487
00:29:08,080 --> 00:29:09,248
You never know.

488
00:29:09,331 --> 00:29:11,416
You've always been shady.

489
00:29:11,500 --> 00:29:14,294
You suck up to Father,
all while plotting to stab me in the back.

490
00:29:14,378 --> 00:29:15,963
What about you?

491
00:29:17,798 --> 00:29:19,841
You told me
you were getting Father a watch,

492
00:29:19,925 --> 00:29:22,261
then secretly went
and bought him a villa in Cancun.

493
00:29:22,344 --> 00:29:23,428
Didn't you?

494
00:29:23,512 --> 00:29:26,223
Why are you bringing that up now?

495
00:29:26,306 --> 00:29:27,474
You're years younger than me,

496
00:29:27,557 --> 00:29:29,601
yet you never miss a chance
to get in my face.

497
00:29:29,685 --> 00:29:31,186
Please lower your voices.

498
00:29:31,270 --> 00:29:32,604
They're ringing down the halls.

499
00:29:32,688 --> 00:29:34,815
What the hell?
What are you doing here?

500
00:29:34,898 --> 00:29:35,983
What the…

501
00:29:36,066 --> 00:29:37,401
Am I not allowed to be here?

502
00:29:37,484 --> 00:29:39,111
I came to inspect a subsidiary.

503
00:29:39,194 --> 00:29:40,779
Have a seat, both of you.

504
00:29:41,655 --> 00:29:43,573
Who the hell are you to tell us to sit?

505
00:29:43,657 --> 00:29:46,952
I'm starting an internal audit
of Chail Food this week.

506
00:29:49,997 --> 00:29:52,124
The Q1 and Q2 accounting data is a mess.

507
00:29:52,207 --> 00:29:53,792
You should've balanced the numbers.

508
00:29:53,875 --> 00:29:55,836
I thought we might
as well pull the past ledgers

509
00:29:55,919 --> 00:29:58,088
and run a full reconciliation.
What do you say?

510
00:29:58,171 --> 00:29:59,381
A full reconciliation?

511
00:29:59,464 --> 00:30:01,675
I mean, why harp on the past?

512
00:30:01,758 --> 00:30:04,469
Shouldn't we be looking forward, not back?

513
00:30:04,553 --> 00:30:05,429
Mun-do.

514
00:30:05,512 --> 00:30:08,557
I promise you I'm not someone
who buckles under

515
00:30:08,640 --> 00:30:10,350
such unsophisticated threats.

516
00:30:15,397 --> 00:30:16,398
My God!

517
00:30:21,236 --> 00:30:24,614
I trust both of you will be
more than happy

518
00:30:24,698 --> 00:30:27,868
to attend Chail Group's
50th anniversary celebration.

519
00:30:27,951 --> 00:30:30,203
Come and be the first to congratulate me.

520
00:30:53,268 --> 00:30:55,520
<i>For the first time in my life as a seer,</i>

521
00:30:55,604 --> 00:30:57,522
<i>I channeled a spirit.</i>

522
00:30:57,606 --> 00:30:59,691
"There is not much time left."

523
00:30:59,775 --> 00:31:03,362
"When the red comet finds its place again,
and your vital energy returns,

524
00:31:03,445 --> 00:31:05,781
it will guide Your Highness's soul."

525
00:31:05,864 --> 00:31:07,199
I definitely received that message

526
00:31:07,282 --> 00:31:09,076
from the spirit that I channeled.

527
00:31:09,159 --> 00:31:12,329
And then I found out
there had been a red comet all along.

528
00:31:12,412 --> 00:31:15,540
They say it's been up there
for about three months now.

529
00:31:16,291 --> 00:31:17,584
And I believe

530
00:31:17,667 --> 00:31:19,294
that's exactly how long you've been here.

531
00:31:19,378 --> 00:31:22,923
I just feel like there might be
some sort of connection there.

532
00:31:23,006 --> 00:31:25,926
<i>And that part about guiding a soul</i>
<i>really bothered me.</i>

533
00:31:27,427 --> 00:31:29,262
<i>There is not much time left.</i>

534
00:31:29,346 --> 00:31:32,682
When the red comet finds its place again,
and your vital energy returns,

535
00:31:32,766 --> 00:31:34,351
it will guide Your Highness's soul.

536
00:31:35,185 --> 00:31:36,603
Back to your body here.

537
00:31:38,939 --> 00:31:40,399
What are you doing out here?

538
00:31:50,700 --> 00:31:52,285
You're unbelievable.

539
00:31:55,080 --> 00:31:57,249
Why did you come out here without a word?

540
00:31:57,332 --> 00:31:58,542
I looked everywhere for you.

541
00:31:58,625 --> 00:32:00,085
Just because.

542
00:32:00,168 --> 00:32:02,129
I wanted to look at the sky.

543
00:32:02,671 --> 00:32:04,673
It's cold. You could've
just looked out the window.

544
00:32:04,756 --> 00:32:05,882
Cha Se-gye.

545
00:32:06,425 --> 00:32:07,676
Look at that.

546
00:32:09,094 --> 00:32:10,929
Stars over Seoul. That's new.

547
00:32:11,012 --> 00:32:12,347
Air quality must be good today.

548
00:32:12,431 --> 00:32:13,348
That right there is

549
00:32:13,432 --> 00:32:15,016
the ill-omened star.

550
00:32:16,601 --> 00:32:18,854
The ill-omened star? Is that a thing?

551
00:32:18,937 --> 00:32:21,565
Even 300 years ago when I lived,

552
00:32:21,648 --> 00:32:24,151
a star like that was in the sky.

553
00:32:24,234 --> 00:32:26,570
They said it threatened the Crown.

554
00:32:26,653 --> 00:32:29,281
It was the star that brought
a blade to my neck.

555
00:32:29,364 --> 00:32:30,365
And now…

556
00:32:31,491 --> 00:32:33,660
there it is again.

557
00:32:37,164 --> 00:32:40,083
That can't be the same star.
That'd be the mightiest load of crap ever.

558
00:32:40,167 --> 00:32:42,335
Astrology, star signs, and all that junk.

559
00:32:42,419 --> 00:32:45,088
It's all just crap that preys
on hopeless people.

560
00:32:45,172 --> 00:32:46,214
Right.

561
00:32:47,007 --> 00:32:48,425
All crap.

562
00:32:51,845 --> 00:32:53,305
Cha Se-gye.

563
00:32:53,388 --> 00:32:54,431
What now?

564
00:32:54,514 --> 00:32:56,099
I want to eat some tofu.

565
00:32:56,183 --> 00:32:57,434
Tofu?

566
00:32:58,894 --> 00:33:00,187
All of a sudden?

567
00:33:00,270 --> 00:33:02,606
I told you over and over
not to get discharged,

568
00:33:02,689 --> 00:33:04,941
but you just completely tuned me out.

569
00:33:05,025 --> 00:33:06,985
Gosh, the broth is so good.

570
00:33:07,736 --> 00:33:10,530
Nothing beats tofu for warding off
trouble with the authorities.

571
00:33:10,614 --> 00:33:12,240
Here, eat up.

572
00:33:14,993 --> 00:33:16,119
Hold on.

573
00:33:16,870 --> 00:33:18,830
You knew I was at the police station?

574
00:33:18,914 --> 00:33:20,665
So you wanted to feed me tofu?

575
00:33:20,749 --> 00:33:23,502
Were I in better health,
I would perform a ritual immediately.

576
00:33:23,585 --> 00:33:26,505
But you would detest that,
so this is the least we could do.

577
00:33:26,588 --> 00:33:29,299
Eat up. Have some of this <i>kalguksu</i> too.

578
00:33:30,008 --> 00:33:30,967
Ridiculous.

579
00:33:32,219 --> 00:33:33,470
I don't want <i>kalguksu.</i>

580
00:33:33,553 --> 00:33:36,264
I'm sick of it. You eat up.

581
00:33:36,348 --> 00:33:38,850
- Sick of it?
- I ate it so much as a kid.

582
00:33:38,934 --> 00:33:41,728
My mom always defaulted to <i>kalguksu.</i>
That's all she ever bought me.

583
00:33:41,811 --> 00:33:43,480
She must've thought I liked it.

584
00:33:43,563 --> 00:33:45,232
But I was just pretending.

585
00:33:48,860 --> 00:33:51,780
But I remember
the last bowl I had with her.

586
00:33:52,614 --> 00:33:54,074
That one wasn't bad.

587
00:33:55,200 --> 00:33:56,409
Every now and then, I remember

588
00:33:56,493 --> 00:33:59,412
and go back to that place,
but it never tastes the same.

589
00:34:02,123 --> 00:34:04,668
Perhaps it is because you had it with her?

590
00:34:04,751 --> 00:34:05,710
What?

591
00:34:05,794 --> 00:34:08,380
No matter how dark the night is,

592
00:34:09,256 --> 00:34:11,258
if someone is by your side,

593
00:34:11,841 --> 00:34:15,011
it is a bit more bearable and less scary.

594
00:34:15,095 --> 00:34:16,805
That is just how it is.

595
00:34:16,888 --> 00:34:18,765
It is not about where you are.

596
00:34:18,848 --> 00:34:20,892
It is about who you are with.

597
00:34:25,647 --> 00:34:27,023
Is that so?

598
00:34:31,403 --> 00:34:32,696
You're right.

599
00:34:33,613 --> 00:34:36,366
I wondered why it was
going down so easily today.

600
00:34:36,449 --> 00:34:38,451
It was because I was with you.

601
00:34:39,452 --> 00:34:41,288
Eating alone really was the problem.

602
00:34:43,748 --> 00:34:45,584
You've always got a rebuttal
for everything.

603
00:34:45,667 --> 00:34:46,918
Eat up.

604
00:34:47,002 --> 00:34:48,753
People might mistake you for the patient.

605
00:34:48,837 --> 00:34:49,796
Here.

606
00:35:20,493 --> 00:35:22,037
What? What's wrong?

607
00:35:23,496 --> 00:35:24,414
What? No.

608
00:35:24,497 --> 00:35:26,082
It is nothing.

609
00:35:37,844 --> 00:35:39,095
What?

610
00:35:45,018 --> 00:35:47,395
I thought you were in the hospital.
What happened?

611
00:35:47,479 --> 00:35:48,730
I was worried about you.

612
00:35:48,813 --> 00:35:51,274
You must have been very busy.

613
00:35:51,358 --> 00:35:52,942
Your complexion looks even…

614
00:35:53,985 --> 00:35:54,944
Truth is,

615
00:35:55,028 --> 00:35:56,529
some lunatic

616
00:35:56,613 --> 00:35:58,698
has been smashing our lights every night.

617
00:35:58,782 --> 00:36:02,535
So I've been on a stakeout for days
trying to catch that bastard.

618
00:36:03,870 --> 00:36:05,580
If I ever catch him…

619
00:36:07,332 --> 00:36:09,751
I'm not going.
I refuse to leave you alone.

620
00:36:09,834 --> 00:36:11,670
What is wrong with you? It is pathetic.

621
00:36:11,753 --> 00:36:13,713
I've always been
pathetic and super clingy.

622
00:36:13,797 --> 00:36:15,382
I can't just leave you here all alone.

623
00:36:15,465 --> 00:36:17,384
So if you refuse to come with me…

624
00:36:17,467 --> 00:36:19,219
Wait. Hold on.

625
00:36:24,349 --> 00:36:26,518
- What the…
- I'm not going either.

626
00:36:26,601 --> 00:36:27,769
Do what you will.

627
00:37:07,434 --> 00:37:09,185
That bed is so cramped.

628
00:37:10,311 --> 00:37:12,272
It is even more cramped down here.

629
00:37:14,065 --> 00:37:15,984
You are as big as a mountain.

630
00:37:19,529 --> 00:37:21,698
It hurts to sleep on the floor.

631
00:37:23,491 --> 00:37:25,034
You're so damn stubborn.

632
00:37:33,626 --> 00:37:36,254
<i>They say it's been up there</i>
<i>for about three months now.</i>

633
00:37:36,337 --> 00:37:38,798
<i>And I believe</i>
<i>that's exactly how long you've been here.</i>

634
00:37:38,882 --> 00:37:41,634
<i>When the red comet finds its place again,</i>
<i>and your vital energy returns,</i>

635
00:37:41,718 --> 00:37:44,262
it will guide Your Highness's soul.

636
00:37:45,472 --> 00:37:47,974
Back to your body here.

637
00:37:48,057 --> 00:37:50,477
After all, you were dragged here
without warning.

638
00:37:50,560 --> 00:37:52,228
You could be dragged out the same way.

639
00:37:52,312 --> 00:37:54,689
With all that necromancy business
guiding your soul.

640
00:38:09,120 --> 00:38:11,664
<i>Does this mean I will truly disappear?</i>

641
00:38:17,629 --> 00:38:19,672
Shin Seo-ri, are you asleep?

642
00:38:22,008 --> 00:38:23,218
You know,

643
00:38:23,301 --> 00:38:26,054
I can say this now. The truth is,

644
00:38:26,137 --> 00:38:27,639
I was a little scared.

645
00:38:29,891 --> 00:38:32,227
While I was waiting
for you at the hospital,

646
00:38:32,310 --> 00:38:34,103
I couldn't sleep at night,

647
00:38:34,187 --> 00:38:36,439
and all sorts of thoughts
ran through my mind.

648
00:38:37,524 --> 00:38:38,691
Like what?

649
00:38:38,775 --> 00:38:40,276
"What if she wakes up

650
00:38:40,360 --> 00:38:42,987
and pushes me away because she's scared?"

651
00:38:43,071 --> 00:38:46,324
"Could I let you go then?"

652
00:38:48,201 --> 00:38:50,495
"I hate even thinking about that."

653
00:38:53,122 --> 00:38:54,833
Dumb thoughts like that.

654
00:38:55,708 --> 00:38:57,210
You really are a fool.

655
00:38:57,710 --> 00:38:59,546
When I think about

656
00:39:00,922 --> 00:39:03,091
how my despair could spread to you

657
00:39:03,174 --> 00:39:04,592
if you get involved with me,

658
00:39:04,676 --> 00:39:06,302
I feel so sorry,

659
00:39:06,386 --> 00:39:08,847
and I find myself doubting I can keep you.

660
00:39:08,930 --> 00:39:10,348
I don't know.

661
00:39:10,431 --> 00:39:12,475
I'm a selfish jerk.

662
00:39:13,810 --> 00:39:16,229
I don't even want to imagine
letting you go.

663
00:39:34,497 --> 00:39:36,833
It's weird. Ever since I met you,

664
00:39:37,667 --> 00:39:39,919
I think I've been getting a little dumber.

665
00:39:40,003 --> 00:39:42,171
Things have become simpler.

666
00:39:42,255 --> 00:39:44,757
And everything I spent
a lifetime running after

667
00:39:44,841 --> 00:39:46,968
all feels worthless now.

668
00:39:55,018 --> 00:39:57,020
Seriously, what am I going to do?

669
00:39:57,812 --> 00:39:59,689
Maybe I'm broken?

670
00:40:15,788 --> 00:40:17,290
Are you?

671
00:40:18,625 --> 00:40:20,084
I guess you are.

672
00:40:21,127 --> 00:40:22,545
You are broken.

673
00:40:23,880 --> 00:40:26,049
If you are broken, you need to be fixed.

674
00:40:26,925 --> 00:40:28,301
How?

675
00:40:29,093 --> 00:40:30,553
Like this.

676
00:40:38,978 --> 00:40:40,396
Cha Se-gye.

677
00:40:40,480 --> 00:40:43,274
No matter what happens
to us in the future,

678
00:40:43,358 --> 00:40:45,109
just remember this one thing.

679
00:40:45,193 --> 00:40:46,903
That I…

680
00:40:49,113 --> 00:40:51,324
truly hold you in my heart.

681
00:40:51,407 --> 00:40:53,534
I will take that with me wherever I go.

682
00:40:53,618 --> 00:40:55,745
And with that one memory,

683
00:40:57,205 --> 00:40:59,040
I will flourish and not wither away.

684
00:41:01,417 --> 00:41:02,418
Promise me.

685
00:41:32,573 --> 00:41:33,741
Can I get some water?

686
00:41:43,751 --> 00:41:45,461
Hey, Ji-hyo.

687
00:41:45,545 --> 00:41:46,754
Here.

688
00:41:46,838 --> 00:41:48,214
Thanks.

689
00:41:51,467 --> 00:41:53,636
<i>Who is that? An extra?</i>

690
00:41:53,720 --> 00:41:56,222
But were we close enough
to drop formalities?

691
00:41:56,305 --> 00:41:57,598
Oh, come on.

692
00:41:57,682 --> 00:42:00,476
When you were the BR Ice Cream Princess,
I was the oak tree.

693
00:42:00,560 --> 00:42:03,187
You know that commercial
from 23 years ago.

694
00:42:03,271 --> 00:42:04,272
The oak tree?

695
00:42:04,355 --> 00:42:05,565
I see.

696
00:42:05,648 --> 00:42:08,609
It's been so long,
so you don't really remember.

697
00:42:08,693 --> 00:42:11,237
Right. That makes sense. Yeah.

698
00:42:15,992 --> 00:42:17,827
Did you have more to say?

699
00:42:18,828 --> 00:42:20,705
Well, I was wondering…

700
00:42:20,788 --> 00:42:22,331
Is Seo-ri doing okay?

701
00:42:23,374 --> 00:42:25,376
Her phone is off, and I can't reach her.

702
00:42:25,460 --> 00:42:27,128
You're in the same agency.

703
00:42:27,211 --> 00:42:29,005
I heard she regained consciousness.

704
00:42:29,088 --> 00:42:31,257
She didn't look that hurt anyway.

705
00:42:32,925 --> 00:42:34,969
Did you go visit her in the hospital?

706
00:42:36,137 --> 00:42:37,930
Well, we're in the same agency,

707
00:42:38,014 --> 00:42:39,891
so it's the least I could do.

708
00:42:39,974 --> 00:42:41,642
Why? Do you want her home address?

709
00:42:41,726 --> 00:42:44,020
No, that would be going overboard.

710
00:42:44,103 --> 00:42:46,105
Plenty of people
are already taking care of her.

711
00:42:46,189 --> 00:42:47,857
Okay. I'll be going now.

712
00:42:47,940 --> 00:42:49,400
You can get back to it.

713
00:42:53,571 --> 00:42:55,990
Hold on, what is Baek Gwang-nam doing?

714
00:42:56,074 --> 00:42:58,034
Is he slacking off somewhere?

715
00:42:59,160 --> 00:43:00,620
Manager Baek Gwang-nam!

716
00:43:00,703 --> 00:43:02,205
Manager Baek Gwang-nam!

717
00:43:02,997 --> 00:43:05,333
Manager Baek Gwang-nam! Manager Baek!

718
00:43:05,416 --> 00:43:06,584
Is being the lead the end-all?

719
00:43:06,667 --> 00:43:09,712
Who does she think she is changing up
the schedule however she wants?

720
00:43:09,796 --> 00:43:12,256
Thanks to her,
Shin Seo-ri was let off the hook.

721
00:43:12,882 --> 00:43:14,717
I heard she got into a fender bender.

722
00:43:14,801 --> 00:43:17,929
If it weren't for Yoon Ji-hyo,
she would've been fired a long time ago.

723
00:43:18,012 --> 00:43:19,222
That's true.

724
00:43:20,139 --> 00:43:23,935
Hold on, did Yoon Ji-hyo postpone
the schedule for Shin Seo-ri's sake?

725
00:43:24,018 --> 00:43:26,229
- Because they're in the same agency?
- As if.

726
00:43:26,312 --> 00:43:27,980
Those two are total arch-enemies.

727
00:43:28,064 --> 00:43:31,859
No. It's one-sided.
Yoon Ji-hyo despises Shin Seo-ri.

728
00:43:31,943 --> 00:43:33,027
Full-on loathing.

729
00:43:34,570 --> 00:43:36,239
There's no full-on loathing.

730
00:43:41,160 --> 00:43:42,286
Never heard of rivals?

731
00:43:42,370 --> 00:43:43,704
Fated counterparts.

732
00:43:43,788 --> 00:43:44,747
Like Ronaldo and Messi.

733
00:43:44,831 --> 00:43:47,166
Kang Baek-ho and Seo Tae-woong.
Lee Seung-yeop and Lee Dae-ho.

734
00:43:47,250 --> 00:43:48,751
- Who are you?
- Me?

735
00:43:49,794 --> 00:43:51,963
I'm Shin Seo-ri's manager.

736
00:43:52,046 --> 00:43:54,132
And Ji-hyo's day-to-day manager. Why?

737
00:43:54,215 --> 00:43:56,008
Let's not go throwing
people's names around

738
00:43:56,092 --> 00:43:58,719
when you don't know
the full story. All right?

739
00:43:58,803 --> 00:44:00,930
Manager Baek Gwang-nam!

740
00:44:01,931 --> 00:44:03,975
- Manager!
- Nice catch.

741
00:44:05,393 --> 00:44:07,854
- What sort of manager…
- What's with him?

742
00:44:07,937 --> 00:44:10,356
- You want me to just eat it?
- As if she weren't bad enough,

743
00:44:10,439 --> 00:44:12,942
now her manager is even acting up?

744
00:44:14,819 --> 00:44:18,364
Seo-ri. Wake up, Seo-ri.

745
00:44:18,447 --> 00:44:20,658
<i>When you wake up from your nap,</i>

746
00:44:20,741 --> 00:44:22,994
<i>we should be home.</i>

747
00:44:35,173 --> 00:44:36,424
Home…

748
00:44:37,341 --> 00:44:39,385
<i>There is not much time left.</i>

749
00:44:39,468 --> 00:44:43,097
When the red comet finds its place again,
and your vital energy returns,

750
00:44:43,181 --> 00:44:45,683
it will guide Your Highness's soul.

751
00:44:45,766 --> 00:44:47,935
<i>Back to your body here.</i>

752
00:44:50,146 --> 00:44:52,690
<i>Does this mean I will truly disappear</i>

753
00:44:53,441 --> 00:44:54,775
<i>from this place?</i>

754
00:44:55,359 --> 00:44:59,655
CHAIL SEOUL HOSPITAL

755
00:45:06,037 --> 00:45:07,914
<i>That's why I want Se-gye</i>

756
00:45:07,997 --> 00:45:09,874
to start a family of his own

757
00:45:09,957 --> 00:45:11,626
and never be lonely again.

758
00:45:11,709 --> 00:45:13,294
That's all I ask.

759
00:45:13,377 --> 00:45:15,755
If that is the case,
you do not need to worry.

760
00:45:15,838 --> 00:45:18,132
I will make sure he is never lonely again.

761
00:45:18,216 --> 00:45:20,259
I have thought about it long and hard.

762
00:45:20,343 --> 00:45:22,345
Why you kept me at a distance.

763
00:45:22,428 --> 00:45:24,931
Hoping Cha Se-gye would start a family…

764
00:45:27,391 --> 00:45:29,769
and not be lonely among other people.

765
00:45:29,852 --> 00:45:31,395
That must be how

766
00:45:31,479 --> 00:45:34,065
you have kept him safe until now.

767
00:45:34,148 --> 00:45:35,775
Foolishly and selfishly.

768
00:45:40,112 --> 00:45:42,782
I was certain it was foolish,
but in the end…

769
00:45:42,865 --> 00:45:44,492
Fine, it's because I'm lonely.

770
00:45:44,575 --> 00:45:47,745
Do not worry.
I will not let you be lonely.

771
00:45:48,663 --> 00:45:51,207
I will make sure you are not alone.

772
00:45:55,628 --> 00:45:57,546
It seems I cannot help it either.

773
00:45:57,630 --> 00:45:59,173
More than anyone,

774
00:45:59,257 --> 00:46:01,801
I do not want him to suffer.

775
00:46:02,635 --> 00:46:07,014
I do not wish to see him wither away,
reaching for the void the way I did.

776
00:46:07,098 --> 00:46:09,100
So do not worry.

777
00:46:09,976 --> 00:46:12,144
Your selfish wish.

778
00:46:13,729 --> 00:46:15,189
I shall make sure to grant it.

779
00:46:46,971 --> 00:46:50,433
A blood alcohol level of 0.12
is grounds for license revocation.

780
00:46:50,516 --> 00:46:52,601
Even if it goes straight
to the prosecutors,

781
00:46:52,685 --> 00:46:53,936
it'll be a suspended indictment.

782
00:46:54,020 --> 00:46:56,397
That's the part I find strange.

783
00:46:56,480 --> 00:46:58,649
It's been less than three months
since his last DUI.

784
00:46:58,733 --> 00:47:00,443
He's highly likely to be indicted.

785
00:47:00,526 --> 00:47:01,444
A lot of gambling debt.

786
00:47:01,527 --> 00:47:04,155
Just two weeks ago,
he was about to lose his truck,

787
00:47:04,238 --> 00:47:07,074
but he paid off all that debt
in one go, a few days ago.

788
00:47:07,158 --> 00:47:09,493
And right after that, he got drunk
and got behind the wheel.

789
00:47:09,577 --> 00:47:12,621
Unless he was determined
to go to prison…

790
00:47:12,705 --> 00:47:14,415
Could he be behind this as well?

791
00:47:17,585 --> 00:47:19,378
You're surprisingly calm.

792
00:47:19,462 --> 00:47:21,672
I've taken so many hits
that my blood's gone cold.

793
00:47:21,756 --> 00:47:23,841
- What about Choi Mun-do?
- It looks like he's planning

794
00:47:23,924 --> 00:47:25,217
to announce the resort project

795
00:47:25,301 --> 00:47:27,636
and cement his position publicly
at the upcoming ceremony.

796
00:47:27,720 --> 00:47:28,596
Also…

797
00:47:29,347 --> 00:47:30,431
Well…

798
00:47:31,057 --> 00:47:33,309
We can't reach the nurse.

799
00:47:33,392 --> 00:47:35,436
She doesn't seem to be at her place.

800
00:47:36,562 --> 00:47:39,106
Gosh, this is so nice.

801
00:47:39,690 --> 00:47:41,525
Oh my, look at that bird.

802
00:47:42,193 --> 00:47:45,196
Hey, Boksun, where are you going?

803
00:47:45,279 --> 00:47:47,615
Why are you going there?
Is something there?

804
00:47:50,409 --> 00:47:51,577
Is that a person?

805
00:47:52,912 --> 00:47:56,207
Please call the police! Call them! Hurry!

806
00:48:00,628 --> 00:48:02,004
Thank you.

807
00:48:02,838 --> 00:48:06,008
<i>Hey, you just got out of the hospital.</i>
<i>Why are you back on set already?</i>

808
00:48:06,092 --> 00:48:07,802
I cannot push it back again.

809
00:48:07,885 --> 00:48:09,095
What if I get fired?

810
00:48:09,178 --> 00:48:11,931
Who's firing who?
Do you know how much I put into that?

811
00:48:12,014 --> 00:48:13,641
<i>Stop talking nonsense and hang up.</i>

812
00:48:13,724 --> 00:48:15,184
See you later.

813
00:48:17,061 --> 00:48:19,480
Is that your boyfriend? Is he worried?

814
00:48:20,231 --> 00:48:22,316
He should worry about his own survival.

815
00:48:22,400 --> 00:48:23,818
His future is so bleak.

816
00:48:25,277 --> 00:48:26,278
Oh right.

817
00:48:27,279 --> 00:48:28,322
Want some?

818
00:48:29,490 --> 00:48:31,033
Walnut pastries.

819
00:48:31,826 --> 00:48:34,620
How sweet. Thinking of me while eating.

820
00:48:34,703 --> 00:48:37,081
Oh right. I heard Yoon Ji-hyo visited you.

821
00:48:37,164 --> 00:48:38,999
Look at you go, Shin Seo-ri.

822
00:48:39,083 --> 00:48:40,751
You even have a top star
looking after you.

823
00:48:40,835 --> 00:48:42,586
Looking after me? As if.

824
00:48:42,670 --> 00:48:44,880
Ms. Hong probably just pushed her
to show her face there.

825
00:48:44,964 --> 00:48:48,050
Still, I think you're really lucky.

826
00:48:48,676 --> 00:48:50,177
Schedule pushed back, job still intact.

827
00:48:50,261 --> 00:48:52,721
Quick recovery, right back on set.

828
00:48:53,389 --> 00:48:56,225
I just want to properly finish
the task I was given.

829
00:48:57,685 --> 00:49:00,813
It is the small courtesy I can give
to the name I borrowed.

830
00:49:02,022 --> 00:49:04,191
I also want to remain
steadfast until the very end.

831
00:49:04,275 --> 00:49:06,110
- Ms. Shin Seo-ri.
- Yes?

832
00:49:06,193 --> 00:49:08,904
The wardrobe team wants you
over at the prop storage.

833
00:49:08,988 --> 00:49:10,239
Really?

834
00:49:11,073 --> 00:49:13,117
Are they looking to settle the score
over the costume?

835
00:49:13,200 --> 00:49:14,076
Who knows?

836
00:49:14,160 --> 00:49:17,079
They might need to fit you
for a new costume.

837
00:49:20,916 --> 00:49:23,043
Hey, where is this wardrobe storage?

838
00:49:23,127 --> 00:49:25,463
It's right over there.

839
00:49:28,632 --> 00:49:30,968
Maybe they want to settle the score.

840
00:49:40,227 --> 00:49:43,314
CHAIL 50TH ANNIVERSARY
CELEBRATION CEREMONY

841
00:49:43,397 --> 00:49:46,817
<i>First, a few words</i>
<i>from Chairman Choi Mun-do.</i>

842
00:49:46,901 --> 00:49:52,656
CHAIL 50TH ANNIVERSARY
CELEBRATION CEREMONY

843
00:49:58,245 --> 00:50:00,581
Distinguished members of the Chail family.

844
00:50:00,664 --> 00:50:03,792
Over the past few days,
we have faced an unprecedented disaster.

845
00:50:03,876 --> 00:50:05,878
There was a tragic accident,

846
00:50:05,961 --> 00:50:09,298
and we had to face a crisis
that shook this company to its core.

847
00:50:09,381 --> 00:50:10,716
However, standing here today,

848
00:50:10,799 --> 00:50:12,760
I will confidently tell you this.

849
00:50:12,843 --> 00:50:14,887
From here on, our new Chail

850
00:50:14,970 --> 00:50:18,682
will follow the path of law,
principle, and justice.

851
00:50:18,766 --> 00:50:20,142
We will usher in a new era,

852
00:50:20,226 --> 00:50:21,852
where the blood and sweat you have shed

853
00:50:22,770 --> 00:50:24,438
is met with fair recognition.

854
00:50:31,153 --> 00:50:33,572
The project that will be
its first cornerstone…

855
00:50:40,454 --> 00:50:42,748
The Songjin Integrated Resort.

856
00:51:12,820 --> 00:51:14,113
<i>With that,</i>

857
00:51:14,196 --> 00:51:16,365
<i>allow me to introduce you all</i>

858
00:51:16,448 --> 00:51:18,701
to a partner with whom
Chail will build its future glory.

859
00:51:18,784 --> 00:51:22,162
Please welcome Ms. Mo Tae-hee
from Mochang with a round of applause.

860
00:51:32,172 --> 00:51:33,173
What's her deal?

861
00:51:33,257 --> 00:51:35,342
Hello, I am Mo Tae-hee.

862
00:51:35,426 --> 00:51:38,596
First, please allow me
to offer congratulations

863
00:51:38,679 --> 00:51:41,432
on your appointment
on behalf of all of us at Mochang.

864
00:51:42,349 --> 00:51:43,976
Going forward, Mochang Group

865
00:51:44,059 --> 00:51:45,894
will stand alongside Chail Group

866
00:51:45,978 --> 00:51:48,397
and do our best to establish ourselves

867
00:51:48,480 --> 00:51:51,567
as a leader in Korea
that defines the global standard.

868
00:51:51,650 --> 00:51:54,570
In that spirit, I would like to share

869
00:51:54,653 --> 00:51:57,197
the honor of this occasion
with a certain someone.

870
00:51:57,281 --> 00:52:00,284
I believe that if anyone can share

871
00:52:00,367 --> 00:52:04,288
the burden of the new Chail
with the chairman, it would be him.

872
00:52:05,497 --> 00:52:06,373
Please come up.

873
00:52:06,457 --> 00:52:08,459
- Isn't that Cha Se-gye?
- It's Cha Se-gye.

874
00:52:31,315 --> 00:52:32,816
Hello, everyone.

875
00:52:33,692 --> 00:52:35,903
I am Cha Se-gye, the newly appointed head

876
00:52:35,986 --> 00:52:39,573
of the TF team tasked with overseeing
the integrated resort development.

877
00:52:42,451 --> 00:52:44,161
It's nice to see you all.

878
00:52:47,414 --> 00:52:48,832
The prodigal son has returned.

879
00:52:54,797 --> 00:52:56,924
Unbelievable. Absolutely unbelievable.

880
00:53:13,899 --> 00:53:16,276
You summoned me, and you are not here?

881
00:53:37,965 --> 00:53:39,758
What do you think you're doing?

882
00:53:41,969 --> 00:53:43,679
I thought I'd give it a try too,

883
00:53:43,762 --> 00:53:45,389
a Trojan Horse.

884
00:53:46,181 --> 00:53:48,976
To catch a thief,
you have to enter their den first.

885
00:53:57,943 --> 00:54:00,154
Ms. Mo, I'm disappointed.

886
00:54:00,237 --> 00:54:02,406
I thought you were a smart businesswoman.

887
00:54:04,658 --> 00:54:05,993
But you're <i>just </i>a woman.

888
00:54:06,076 --> 00:54:07,786
I'm even more disappointed.

889
00:54:07,870 --> 00:54:11,915
I don't care much for the old approach
of chasing money by brute force.

890
00:54:18,922 --> 00:54:20,716
Dad.

891
00:54:21,550 --> 00:54:22,760
Seo-jun.

892
00:54:26,805 --> 00:54:28,223
Let's go.

893
00:54:36,148 --> 00:54:38,901
How do you feel?
Your mission was a success.

894
00:54:39,568 --> 00:54:42,446
I don't feel anything.
I haven't done anything yet.

895
00:54:43,489 --> 00:54:45,240
Still, we've planted our flag,
thanks to you.

896
00:54:45,324 --> 00:54:47,785
I look forward to great things,
Ms. Mo Tae-hee.

897
00:54:50,329 --> 00:54:51,955
Mr. Cha Se-gye.

898
00:54:55,959 --> 00:54:58,420
- Can I help you?
- We're going to need you to come with us.

899
00:54:58,504 --> 00:55:00,798
We have some questions for you
regarding a death.

900
00:55:00,881 --> 00:55:02,090
A death?

901
00:55:02,174 --> 00:55:03,467
You know Ms. An Seong-hui?

902
00:55:03,550 --> 00:55:05,719
She was found dead this morning.

903
00:55:05,803 --> 00:55:09,097
Some items belonging to you
were also discovered at her home.

904
00:55:09,181 --> 00:55:11,141
Trouble seems to be following you around.

905
00:55:11,225 --> 00:55:14,311
Your grandfather is in the hospital,
and your company was taken over.

906
00:55:15,771 --> 00:55:17,898
<i>Shin Seo-ri, wake up.</i>

907
00:55:17,981 --> 00:55:19,733
<i>Wake up, Shin Seo-ri!</i>

908
00:55:19,817 --> 00:55:22,277
You sure you can handle that?

909
00:55:23,946 --> 00:55:25,989
The questioning will have to wait.

910
00:55:26,073 --> 00:55:28,325
- Hey.
- Se-gye!

911
00:55:36,917 --> 00:55:39,878
How long are they going to make me wait?

912
00:55:40,504 --> 00:55:42,089
I am so sleepy.

913
00:55:47,219 --> 00:55:48,220
CHA SE-GYE

914
00:55:54,351 --> 00:55:56,687
<i>Shin Seo-ri, where are you?</i>
<i>Are you still on set?</i>

915
00:55:56,770 --> 00:55:57,688
What now?

916
00:55:57,771 --> 00:55:59,898
Are there people around?
Anyone suspicious?

917
00:56:00,482 --> 00:56:02,818
No one is here. I am alone. Why?

918
00:56:02,901 --> 00:56:04,236
Just wait there. I'm on my way.

919
00:56:04,319 --> 00:56:06,655
Go to your car right now.

920
00:56:06,738 --> 00:56:08,240
What is with the fussing?

921
00:56:08,323 --> 00:56:09,700
Worry about yourself--

922
00:56:17,374 --> 00:56:18,542
Goodness.

923
00:56:29,970 --> 00:56:32,264
What's taking her so long?

924
00:56:36,768 --> 00:56:39,187
<i>The phone you are trying</i>
<i>to reach has been turned off…</i>

925
00:56:39,271 --> 00:56:40,480
What the…

926
00:56:44,735 --> 00:56:47,070
- Excuse me.
- Yes?

927
00:56:47,613 --> 00:56:48,780
Is Seo-ri inside?

928
00:56:48,864 --> 00:56:50,532
She left after a call from her boyfriend.

929
00:56:50,616 --> 00:56:51,742
Really?

930
00:56:51,825 --> 00:56:54,995
She did this last time.
She must've sneaked off on a date again.

931
00:56:55,078 --> 00:56:57,956
- Thank you.
- Take care.

932
00:57:23,315 --> 00:57:26,193
- Good work today.
- Thank you.

933
00:57:34,534 --> 00:57:36,328
Wow.

934
00:57:37,287 --> 00:57:39,790
Parents are always the problem.

935
00:57:47,965 --> 00:57:51,677
Is this how they want to settle the score?

936
00:57:53,178 --> 00:57:54,680
Jeez.

937
00:58:02,479 --> 00:58:04,314
Why am I so dizzy?

938
00:58:25,752 --> 00:58:26,878
<i>What's that?</i>

939
00:58:27,421 --> 00:58:28,755
This?

940
00:58:28,839 --> 00:58:31,717
Photos of Shin Seo-ri
as a child actor, before that accident.

941
00:58:31,800 --> 00:58:33,552
The car accident she was in as a kid?

942
00:58:33,635 --> 00:58:37,472
After that, her acting was terrible,
and she hit rock bottom.

943
00:58:38,598 --> 00:58:40,100
Right.

944
00:58:42,269 --> 00:58:46,314
I had a hell of a time keeping
the press quiet back then.

945
00:58:46,398 --> 00:58:47,524
Why?

946
00:58:48,984 --> 00:58:50,527
There is someone in here!

947
00:58:50,610 --> 00:58:52,320
There is someone in here!

948
00:58:52,404 --> 00:58:54,406
Someone, please open the door!

949
00:58:54,489 --> 00:58:57,743
There is someone in here!

950
00:58:58,660 --> 00:58:59,828
Please open the door!

951
00:59:00,328 --> 00:59:02,080
There is someone in here!

952
00:59:09,087 --> 00:59:10,464
<i>Help!</i>

953
00:59:10,547 --> 00:59:12,758
<i>Is anyone out there?</i>

954
00:59:12,841 --> 00:59:14,968
<i>Someone is in here!</i>

955
00:59:16,887 --> 00:59:18,055
<i>Seo-ri.</i>

956
00:59:18,138 --> 00:59:19,765
Seo-ri, wake up.

957
00:59:19,848 --> 00:59:21,058
Take this and go to sleep.

958
00:59:21,141 --> 00:59:23,727
<i>It wasn't actually a car accident.</i>

959
00:59:23,810 --> 00:59:26,354
<i>They were always taking advances</i>
<i>on her appearance fees.</i>

960
00:59:26,438 --> 00:59:28,482
<i>Apparently, they ran some business</i>
<i>into the ground.</i>

961
00:59:28,565 --> 00:59:30,108
You're basically telling us to die here.

962
00:59:30,192 --> 00:59:33,153
When you wake up from your nap,
we should be home.

963
01:00:03,141 --> 01:00:04,434
Mom!

964
01:00:06,144 --> 01:00:08,897
<i>The child breadwinner image</i>
<i>was acceptable,</i>

965
01:00:08,980 --> 01:00:10,941
<i>but a family suicide</i>

966
01:00:11,024 --> 01:00:13,151
<i>is just too dark.</i>

967
01:00:13,735 --> 01:00:16,321
<i>She was still</i>
<i>the Nation's Little Sister, after all.</i>

968
01:00:17,531 --> 01:00:19,116
Help!

969
01:00:19,199 --> 01:00:21,159
Is anyone out there?

970
01:00:21,243 --> 01:00:22,869
Someone is in here!

971
01:00:24,412 --> 01:00:25,497
Dad!

972
01:00:25,580 --> 01:00:26,998
Mom!

973
01:00:39,386 --> 01:00:40,971
Help…

974
01:01:06,079 --> 01:01:07,497
Shin Seo-ri.

975
01:01:09,291 --> 01:01:11,293
Shin Seo-ri, wake up.

976
01:01:11,376 --> 01:01:13,003
Shin Seo-ri.

977
01:01:13,503 --> 01:01:14,588
Shin Seo-ri!

978
01:01:16,715 --> 01:01:18,383
I was just trapped again.

979
01:01:19,509 --> 01:01:20,927
I was trapped.

980
01:01:22,095 --> 01:01:24,264
It felt like I was dying.

981
01:01:28,268 --> 01:01:30,770
I know. Open your eyes. Look at me.

982
01:01:30,854 --> 01:01:33,356
Shin Seo-ri, look at me. Look!

983
01:01:33,440 --> 01:01:35,442
Shin Seo-ri, look at me. Open your eyes!

984
01:01:51,917 --> 01:01:53,335
You're okay.

985
01:01:54,461 --> 01:01:55,712
You're okay.

986
01:01:58,632 --> 01:01:59,966
Shin Seo-ri, look at me.

987
01:02:00,800 --> 01:02:01,801
I'm right here.

988
01:02:11,645 --> 01:02:14,105
Don't worry. Nothing happened.

989
01:02:16,399 --> 01:02:18,026
I'm right here.

990
01:02:20,237 --> 01:02:21,696
Who do you think you are?

991
01:02:22,405 --> 01:02:23,698
Who are you to…

992
01:02:25,533 --> 01:02:26,910
<i>Protect him.</i>

993
01:02:26,993 --> 01:02:28,411
I will be leaving soon anyway.

994
01:02:28,495 --> 01:02:30,497
Are you saying you're going to break up?

995
01:02:32,123 --> 01:02:34,501
Yes. You will not be able to find me.

996
01:02:35,835 --> 01:02:38,964
<i>I never had much to my name to begin with,</i>

997
01:02:40,090 --> 01:02:41,591
<i>so I thought</i>

998
01:02:42,133 --> 01:02:44,928
<i>my feelings would be easy to discard.</i>

999
01:02:45,011 --> 01:02:48,515
<i>I thought it would be easy.</i>

1000
01:02:49,933 --> 01:02:51,810
<i>But when you act like this…</i>

1001
01:02:52,978 --> 01:02:54,604
<i>When you keep…</i>

1002
01:02:56,690 --> 01:02:59,401
<i>making me want to live.</i>

1003
01:03:03,863 --> 01:03:05,824
What am I supposed to do?

1004
01:03:08,076 --> 01:03:10,704
What do you want from me?

1005
01:03:57,042 --> 01:04:00,503
MY ROYAL NEMESIS

1006
01:04:30,825 --> 01:04:33,286
<i>You're not going anywhere alone today.</i>
<i>Resistance is futile.</i>

1007
01:04:33,370 --> 01:04:36,122
<i>- Your </i>hwagyeong<i> has been awakened?</i>
<i>- You were back in Joseon.</i>

1008
01:04:36,206 --> 01:04:37,457
My name is Kang Dan-sim.

1009
01:04:38,083 --> 01:04:41,378
<i>Could you keep smiling like that</i>
<i>even if you knew I would disappear?</i>

1010
01:04:41,461 --> 01:04:44,255
<i>Because waiting without knowing the end</i>
<i>is just too hard.</i>

1011
01:04:44,339 --> 01:04:46,716
<i>Ms. Nam Ok-sun is not doing well.</i>

1012
01:04:47,759 --> 01:04:49,594
<i>I'm told the Chairman has just woken up.</i>

1013
01:04:49,677 --> 01:04:52,222
<i>If you decide to choose her,</i>
<i>you don't have much time left.</i>

1014
01:04:52,305 --> 01:04:53,431
I am going back.

1015
01:04:53,515 --> 01:04:56,267
<i>You turned someone barely holding it</i>
<i>together into a lovesick moron.</i>

1016
01:04:56,351 --> 01:04:58,061
Damn it.

1017
01:05:01,815 --> 01:05:03,817
Subtitle translation by Justin S. Kim
